    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_14_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 997.1 Carrera S featuring the M97.01 3.8L flat-six. This naturally aspirated powerplant delivers a linear torque curve and a visceral 7,200 RPM redline. The G97 6-speed manual transaxle provides precise shift gates, complemented by the factory PASM (Porsche Active Suspension Management) for optimized damping during high-G cornering. Recent preventative maintenance includes an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a multi-point borescope inspection confirming no signs of cylinder bore scoring. The DME report shows no Range 4-6 overrevs, ensuring the valvetrain integrity remains uncompromised. This is a high-performance driver\u2019s example with a firm pedal feel and immediate throttle response, ideal for those who prioritize chassis dynamics and powertrain health.",
